    "John T. Carroll": ", supplying the unexpressed verb (\u201cyour body [will\nbe] deprived of light\u201d). I read the present tense throughout vv. 34\u201335, with a shift to the\nfuture in the conditional sentence of",
    "John Trapp": "The Holy One of God ] The pope will needs be called \"Most Holy\"; and so lifts up himself above Christ.\n34. The Holy One of God] The pope will needs be called \"Most Holy\"; and so lifts up himself above Christ.\n34. My meat is to do the will ] Job, #Job 23:12 , preferred it before his necessary food, that should keep him alive. So did Christ, when disappointed of a breakfast at the barren fig tree, and coming hungry into the city, he went not into an eating house, but into the temple, where he taught the people most part of that day, #Mt 21:17,23 .\nVer."
